5|$|<b>Satellite</b> <b>observations</b> {{record a}} {{decrease}} in snow-covered areas since the 1960s, when satellites when <b>satellite</b> <b>observations</b> began. In some areas, including China, snow cover has increased. In some regions such as China, a trend of increasing snow cover has been observed from 1978 to 2006. These changes are attributed to global climate change, which may lead to earlier melting and less aea coverage. However, in some areas {{there may be an}} increase in snow depth because of higher temperatures for latitudes north of 40Â°. For the Northern Hemisphere as a whole the mean monthly snow-cover extent has been decreasing by 1.3% per decade.|$|E
